bio.experienceSummary: I am a fun loving, caring and responsible person looking for child care opportunities in the city! Not only have I been babysitting and nannying since high school, I am also a registered nurse! I absolutely adore children, especially my nieces and nephew who I have watched by myself full time for a full week. I love to have fun with the kids and have a blast finding clever ways to make games out of chores and cleaning :)

Hello, wonderful families! I'm Jasmine a warm and dedicated caregiver with over seven years of experience in childcare and a BA in Psychology/Education. My background includes four years as an elementary school teacher.

I provide a safe and nurturing environment for children of all ages. My teaching experience has equipped me with the patience and knowledge to assist with homework, offer personalized tutoring, and create fun and engaging activities.

I am passionate about fostering a fun, educational, and supportive space where every child can explore their interests and develop their strengths. My goal is to contribute positively to your children's development.

I look forward to speaking with and making every day enriching and enjoyable for your children!

description.originalText: Jasmine is one of the kindest and most attentive caregivers I've ever had the pleasure of knowing. Her gentle nature and exceptional multitasking abilities complement her warm and easy-going personality. Despite the challenges of caring for a six-month-old and a toddler, Jasmine seamlessly became an integral part of our family. I wholeheartedly recommend her to any family in need of a caring and dependable nanny.

bio.experienceSummary: I currently work in higher education at NYU, where I completed my BA and MA in International Relations in 2021 and 2022, respectively. I have extensive experience in childcare, after-school programs, and tutoring services over my career and love to support students. I've worked with kids from infants through college with varying learning accessibility needs, and am enthusiastic about building joy and creativity into learning!

Hi! My name is Kat and I'm looking for part time work as a nanny to supplement my income. I've been babysitting since I was 13 and have worked for various families throughout my time in high school and college. I've also worked as a camp counselor and was in charge of the 7 yr old division (roughly 30 girl supervised by myself and one co-counselor). In the summer of 2023 I worked on a farm in Italy and assisted with the child care of a 5-month-old, 11-month-old, and 3-year-old. I can help with babysitting, laundry, running errands, meal prep, cleaning, and tutoring. Please reach out if you think I'd be a good fit!

description.originalText: Catherine was great with our little girl. So patient and played with her the entire time. Would definitely use her again.

bio.experienceSummary:
I am a caring, compassionate, and creative young woman who loves to care for babies and children of all ages. I grew up in upstate NY and spent my teen years babysitting for all the families in the neighborhood. I have lived in NYC for the past 9 years working in the fashion industry and am currently training to be a birth doula. I am passionate about empowering birthing mothers and supporting them through a peaceful and satisfying birth experience. Plus I love babies! :)

I also love being creative and doing craft and cooking projects with the children I care for. I am also happy to do light cleaning, laundry, cooking, errands, care for pets, or anything else you need help with around the house!

I am a warm, bubbly, bright energy. Love me some babies and baby therapy. I am an aunt to 17 nieces and nephews, been babysitting and nannying professionally for over 18 years now. I have experience with newborns all the way to late teenagers. I am a regular tutor for middle & high school kids as well: I teach math, science and English. I am looking forward to meeting your family :)

description.originalText: Absolutely adore Salma! First time leaving our baby with a babysitter and Salma was extremely caring and trustworthy. Any family would be lucky to have such a lovely person caring for their little ones!

bio.experienceSummary: Hi, I'm Erika. I was a third grade teacher for the past 5 years and transitioned to full time nannying this school year. I hold a bachelors degree in childhood education and a masters degree in special education. In addition to my experience in the classroom, I have babysat for many families with children of all ages (newborns to teenagers) and worked for four summers at sleep away camp. I have also tutored children, worked in after school programs and worked at day camp for three summers. I greatly enjoy working with and caring for children. I am available to babysit on Fridays and the weekend. I have no problem with taking children out, preparing meals, providing homework assistance, facilitating games and activities, and taking care of bath time and bedtime. I am more than happy to help your family in any way I can:)

description.originalText: Erika is an absolute angel! We traveled to NYC so that I could undergo a pretty extensive surgery. Erika went above and beyond to care for and entertain our 4 and 2 year olds over the course of multiple days. She was so flexible, communicative and helpful. It was such a relief to know the kids were safe and in good hands, especially being in a new city that we are unfamiliar with. Erika is a wonderful and trustworthy caregiver whom anyone would be lucky to have!

bio.experienceSummary:
As a nurturing and experienced childcare provider with five years of experience, I find joy in supporting families by offering reliable care for their children. My passion for working with children stems from my positive experiences in previous babysitting roles and my natural inclination to create a safe and nurturing environment for them.

I am known for my patience, creativity, and friendly nature, which allows me to build strong relationships with the children in my care and their families. I prioritize open communication with parents, providing regular updates and utilizing their preferred communication method to address any issues or share daily highlights.

Well-versed in enforcing household rules, I ensure a structured and consistent environment for the children. My approach to play includes a variety of activities, including outdoor sports, board games, and educational games that promote learning and development.

description.displayText: Sky was the best nanny I had for L! She worked full time and was always very punctual and hard-working. She provided invaluable assistance when I returned to work following my maternity leave. Not only did she know how to care of my 3-month-old infant, but I also always felt safe entrusting my child to her care and never encountered any issues. Sky was patient and helped L adjust so well after she began. She was a very kind and caring person, and it hurt when we were moving and couldn't continue with her care.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi moms and dads,  I am a fun loving, responsible and reliable 25-year-old. I am currently going into my first year of Law school . I have lovingly cooked, cleaned, played with , educated and cared for two girls ages 3 -5. I also tutored and assisted several children ages 4-10 with assignments for subjects like math, science, reading, art and history as an after school counselor. carefully followed the parents instructions regarding schedules, chores, discipline, and free time. recently I worked as a para, where I was assigned as a one to one. I fostered a safe and loving environment for a child with special needs exercising skills in patience, attention to detail, and de-escalation. I am confident in providing routines, cooking, organizing activities, helping with homework, bath time and bedtime. Coming from a huge family I love working with children because it gives me joy. My main availability is week nights and weekends. I look forward to hearing from you

Hello dear parents, I am in my early 30s. I am able to babysit in English, German, Russian or Ukrainian - it's up to your preference. I have 15+ years of experience as a babysitter and tutor. I have cared for infants, toddlers as well as teenagers, so I am very comfortable with any age group. I've also cared for twins. I spent most of my college years tutoring kids grades 1-12, supervising homework and preparing them for tests and exams. Moreover, I am experienced in teaching the English and German languages. I describe myself as an active and joyful babysitter with two priorities: following the parents' rules in a kind manner, and making sure your little ones are having an awesome time. I have babysat dozens of kids over the past decade and built special bonds with every single one of them.

description.originalText:
We had the immense pleasure of having Elina take care of our two children for two years, and I cannot recommend her highly enough. When she started with us, our eldest was 3 years old, and our youngest was just 7 months old. From day one, Elina proved herself to be the perfect mother's hand.

Elina's dedication, warmth, and professionalism are truly unparalleled. She has a natural ability to connect with children, making them feel safe, loved, and entertained. Our eldest child thrived under her care, developing new skills and confidence each day. Elina's gentle and nurturing approach was particularly invaluable with our baby, ensuring a smooth and happy transition through those crucial early months and beyond.

Elina is incredibly reliable and always goes above and beyond to ensure our children are well-cared for and engaged in meaningful activities. Whether it's creative play, educational games, or simply providing a comforting presence, Elina handles it all with grace and enthusiasm. Her attention to detail and proactive attitude gave us peace of mind, knowing that our children were in the best hands possible.

Additionally, Elina's excellent communication and organizational skills made coordinating schedules and discussing our children's progress a breeze. She consistently kept us informed and involved, fostering a strong partnership between us as parents and her as a caregiver.

In short, Elina has been a blessing to our family. Her love, care, and dedication have made a lasting positive impact on our children's lives. We are incredibly grateful for her time with us and wholeheartedly recommend her to any family in need of exceptional childcare.

Thank you, Elina, for everything!
